-- Argentina, Kazakhstan, Serbia, Canada Win in Davis Cup Doubles
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-04-07T04:17:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-06/argentina-takes-davis-cup-lead-as-kazakhstan-avoids-elimination.html
Argentina  won yesterday’s doubles
match to take a 2-1 lead over France in the Davis Cup
quarterfinals, as Kazakhstan avoided elimination against
defending champion Czech Republic.  David Nalbandian and Horacio Zeballos beat Julien Benneteau
and Michael Llodra 3-6, 7-6 (7-3), 7-5, 6-3 to put Argentina in
front in the best-of-five matchup in Buenos Aires. Yuriy Schukin
and Andrey Golubev beat Radek Stepanek and Jan Hajek 7-6, (7-2),
6-4, 6-3 in Astana, Kazakhstan, to leave the host trailing 2-1.  After the remaining quarterfinals,  Serbia  has a 2-1 lead
over the U.S. and Canada has a 2-1 advantage over Italy.  All four matchups will be decided in today’s two reverse
singles matches with the winners advancing to the semifinals of
the top team event in men’s tennis.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  